# Per-machine zsh overrides. Copy to .zshrc.local and uncomment what applies.
# Sourced at the very end of .zshrc, so anything here wins.
#
#   cp .zshrc.local.example .zshrc.local
#
# Rule of thumb: if a block depends on a specific app being installed on THIS
# machine (rather than on the OS), it belongs here, not in tracked .zshrc.

# --- Private overlay (companion repo + secret manager) ------------------------
# This file is the per-machine bootstrap. Anything private or worth syncing lives
# OUTSIDE the public repo, in two places:
#
#   1. Companion repo — a PRIVATE git repo (e.g. ~/.dotfiles-private) holding work
#      aliases, private functions, and gh-dash work repo paths. Synced across
#      machines via its own remote. Source its entrypoint here:
# [[ -f "$HOME/.dotfiles-private/init.zsh" ]] && source "$HOME/.dotfiles-private/init.zsh"
#
#   2. Secret manager — actual credentials (see Secrets section below). Never
#      commit real secrets to any repo, public or private.
#
# Machine-local-only scripts (not worth syncing) can also live in the gitignored
# dotfiles subdir zsh/local/ and be sourced from there.

# --- Work / project shortcuts -------------------------------------------------

# Example: a one-shot "update my work stack" alias for a repo on this machine.
# alias aioupdate="cd ~/Desktop/Projects/work/my-stack && git pull --rebase && make clean && make build"

# --- IDE aliases (only if these IDEs are installed) ---------------------------

# alias wb="webstorm"
# alias code="code-insiders"

# --- Node ecosystem -----------------------------------------------------------

# nvm — run the official installer first, then uncomment:
# export NVM_DIR="$HOME/.nvm"
# [ -s "$NVM_DIR/nvm.sh" ] && \. "$NVM_DIR/nvm.sh"
# [ -s "$NVM_DIR/bash_completion" ] && \. "$NVM_DIR/bash_completion"

# bun
# export BUN_INSTALL="$HOME/.bun"
# [ -d "$BUN_INSTALL/bin" ] && export PATH="$BUN_INSTALL/bin:$PATH"
# [ -s "$BUN_INSTALL/_bun" ] && source "$BUN_INSTALL/_bun"

